This article describes the setup of an Intel Core 2 Solo/Duo/Quad processor.

== 32-bit vs 64-bit ==
This processor supports both the 32-bit and 64-bit mode. You read about general pros and cons at the [[Wikipedia:64-bit#32-bit_vs_64-bit|Wikipedia]]. By now only very few applications don't support 64-bit mode or work in a 32-bit compatibility mode.

== Installation ==

=== BIOS ===
With a dual or quad core check first, if all of them are enabled:
{{Cmd|cat /proc/cpuinfo}}
If not, enable options like ''<code>APIC</code>'', ''<code>MultiCore</code>'', etc. in your [[BIOS]].

=== Kernel ===

You need to activate the following kernel options.

For a single-core processor:

{{KernelBox|1=
Processor type and features  --->
    Subarchitecture Type ()  --->
        (X) PC-compatible
    Processor family ()  --->
        (X) Core 2/newer Xeon
}}

For a dual- or quad-core processor:

{{KernelBox|1=
Processor type and features  --->
    [*] Symmetric multi-processing support
    Subarchitecture Type ()  --->
        (X) PC-compatible
    Processor family ()  --->
        (X) Core 2/newer Xeon

    dual-core
    (2) Maximum number of CPUs (2-256)

    quad-core
    (4) Maximum number of CPUs (2-256)
}}

=== Software ===

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=|lang=bash|1=
CPU_FLAGS_X86="mmx sse sse2 sse3 ssse3"
}}

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=Penryn and newer|lang=bash|1=
CPU_FLAGS_X86="mmx sse sse2 sse3 ssse3 sse4 sse4a sse4_1"
}}

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=CFLAGS|lang=bash|1=
# Note: -fomit-frame-pointer only makes a difference on x86 since it is included in -O2 on amd64
CFLAGS="-march=native -O2 -pipe -fomit-frame-pointer"
CXXFLAGS="${CFLAGS}"
}}

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=MAKEOPTS (Intel Core 2 Solo)|lang=bash|1=
MAKEOPTS="-j2"
}}

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=MAKEOPTS (Intel Core 2 Duo)|lang=bash|1=
MAKEOPTS="-j3"
}}

{{FileBox|filename=[[:/etc/portage/make.conf]]|title=MAKEOPTS (Intel Core 2 Quad)|lang=bash|1=
MAKEOPTS="-j5"
}}

